==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin 'Mort'.  Presumably, that which will kill you if you don't treat it?
===Noun===
'''Morbidity''' (plural: ''morbidities'')
# What desease, illness, ailment or problem a patient has (that is being discussed, or addressed, or has a service being applied toward.)


Example: When entering a service or procedure, clerks must be sure they apply the service code to the correct morbidity, especially when the patient is being treated for several different illnesses.  

